========
gitHub.com/4rthurcyber08/rivan_day2

whatismyipaddress.com

How to shorten IPv6 Addresses
1. Leading zeroes must be dropped.
   :000a:  > :a:
2. Consecutive zeroes become a double colon
   :0000:0000: > ::


1. 000a:000c:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000/64 =
	a:c::/64
2. 0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000/0 = 
        ::/0	= Default Gateway IPv6
3. fe80:0000:0000:0000:000a:0000:0000:000f/64 =
	fe80::a:0:0:f/64 = Link Local
4. 2002:6500:0000:3000:0000:0000:0000:0000/64 = 
	2001:6500:0:3000::/64 = Reserved Public IPv6 add
5. 0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0001/128 = 
	::1/128 = Loopback
6. ff00:0000:0000:beef:a00a:0aa0:0000:0000/8 = 
         ff00::beef:a00a:aa0:0:0/8

 Bin   Hex(Base 16)   Deci (Base 10)
0000    0             0
0001    1             1
0010    2             2
0011    3             3
0100    4             4
0101    5             5
0110    6             6
0111    7             7
1000    8             8
1001    9             9
1010    A             10
1011    B             11
1100    C             12
1101    D     13
1110    E     14
1111    F     15
       10     16









/7 = F   E
      8i 4i 2i  1i
      0 0 0|     0

/7 = 1st Hextet, 2nd Hexadecimal, 2i


/50 = 4th Hextet, 1st Hexadecimal, 4i

/69 = (5th Hextet, 2nd Hexdecimal, 8i)

=====
Subnet 16 departments using 2001:fd8::/64
C:
 16 = 4 bits
A:
 /64 + 4 = /68 (5th Hextet, 1st Hexadecimal, 1i)
I:
2001:fd8::/64
Long version = 2001:0fd8:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000/68 = First
   2001:fd8::/68
2001:0fd8:0000:0000:1000:0000:0000:0000/68
   2001:fd8:0:0:1000::/68
2001:0fd8:0000:0000:2000:0000:0000:0000/68
   2001:fd8:0:0:2000::/68
2001:0fd8:0000:0000:3000:0000:0000:0000/68
   2001:fd8:0:0:3000::/68
2001:0fd8:0000:0000:4000:0000:0000:0000/68
   2001:fd8:0:0:4000::/68

!@Edge
conf t
ipv6 unicast-routing
int lo200
ipv6 add 2001:fd8::1/68
int lo201
ipv6 add 2001:fd8:0:0:1000::1/68
int lo202
ipv6 add 2001:fd8:0:0:2000::1/68
end

conf t
int lo205
ipv6 add 2001:fd8:0:0:6FFF:FFFF:FFFF:FFFF/68


Broadcast = Anycast (Network/last 128 ip add)











=====
Subnet 200 departments using 2001:fd8::/101
C: 200 = 8bits 
A: /101 + 8 bits = /109 (7th Hextet, 4th Hex, 8i)
I:
2001:0fd8:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000/109 = First
2001:0fd8:0000:0000:0000:0000:0008:0000/109 = 2nd
2001:0fd8:0000:0000:0000:0000:0010:0000/109 = 3rd
2001:0fd8:0000:0000:0000:0000:0018:0000/109 = First
2001:0fd8:0000:0000:0000:0000:0020:0000/109 = First
2001:0fd8:0000:0000:0000:0000:0028:0000/109 = First



